9:
It's a festival they're about to hold in
Palpebra. People dress up in
costumes and eat candy together.
13:
Costumes? That sounds pretty fun,
actually.
17:
I'm MORE interested in how
elemental gems will react within the
bounds of such an atypical
environment.
22:
It's always about research with you,
huh...
24:
Well, they'll be holding the festival
for a couple days, so let's pick a day
we're all free and go together!
29:
Oh, great idea! This will be so much
fun!
34:
Maybe I should outfit myself with
some extra parts for the occasion...
42: Oh my gosh! So THIS is Halloween!
45:
We should be careful not to get 
separated. 
There's a lot of people here tonight.
49:
Don't worry! While I was swapping
out parts, I made sure to upgrade
my sensors too. I can locate
everyone no matter where they are!
54:
Oh? Now that sounds interesting. 
Do tell me more. Actually, why don't 
you let me disassemble you 
just a LITTLE bit?
59:
Eep! Y-you need to get permission
from my managers if you wanna do
that!
64:
Hmm, this calls for another angle.
Today's Halloween, so... Trick or treat!
68:
Wh-what? But... I don't have
anything on me!
72:
Then THAT means I get to tinker with
you as much as I want!
77:
I'm pretty sure that doesn't count as
a trick!
103:
What did I say about running,
children?
106:
Oh! I didn't know you all came to the
festival too!
109:
Hey, Corinna. Are these kids from the
orphanage?
112:
Yes. I'm sorry to be a bother, but if
you could humor them... They've
been looking forward to the festival!
*giggle*
117:
Here you go. These ones are very
tasty.
121:
*laugh* Oh, they're so cute, with
their little soft little cheeks and tiny
costumes!
126:
Maybe we also should've dressed
up. I'm starting to feel like we didn't
put in enough effort.
131:
I don't get it. What kinda festival is
this? What's the point of all the
candy and pumpkins and undead
stuff anyway?
135:
Well, all sorts of people wander into
Palpebra, and over time, their
varying cultures and traditions
mixed together—
145:
Hello, Corinna. And everyone else
too.
149:
Shouldn't you lead with "trick or
treat"? Your costume is adorable, by
the way.
153:
Th-thank you. Your costume. Is very
good too.
157:
Wait, you two know each other? 
I wouldn't have expected it.
160:
I visit the orphanage for work.
Sometimes.
169:
I'm sorry, Falsche. There's really no
reason for him to be so scared...
173:
It's not your fault. My delivery was
very recent, after all.
177:
Ahh... I assume you delivered a
memento from the Kaleidoscope to
the orphanage?
180:
Yes. I must seem like the grim
reaper. To the children who believe
their parents still live.
184:
The only thing GRIM about you is
your opinion of yourself!
189:
Y-yeah! Things like mementos—stuff
to remember people by... They're
important!
193:
If you ever need to sing a requiem,
I'll join you!
197:
Um... I think I will refrain from singing.
It is embarrassing.
204:
I appreciate the thought. Your
singing is lovely.
209:
Falsche, are you guys busy after
this? We were planning on exploring
the festival a little more—
212:
I'm sorry. I have. Something I need to
do.
217:
Speaking of which... Has anyone
seen a figure running around with a
pumpkin on their head?
222:
I'm afraid not... Are you expecting
some kind of trouble?
226:
Not expecting. There is already
trouble.
230:
There are a lot of people dressed up.
In Palpebra right now.
232:
And a lot of them are. The actual
undead.
